 said there was `` ample support '' for a lower court 's finding `` of a predominantly religious purpose '' behind the displays .", "`` Invocation of the almighty by our public figures , at all levels of government , remains commonplace , '' Scalia wrote , noting that even inside the Supreme Court building , Moses is depicted holding the Ten Commandments and that court sessions open with a clerk proclaiming `` God save the United States and this honorable court . ''"]}]
