 , Cassini will perform a course change to avoid following the probe into Titan .', 'Friday evening , tension-loaded springs will push Huygens away from Cassini on a free-fall toward Titan .']}, {'file_name': 'APW_ENG_20041225.0006', 'file_top_sent': ["Next week Cassini will make a course change to avoid following Huygens into Titan 's atmosphere .", "The international Cassini spacecraft launched a probe on a three-week free-fall toward Saturn 's mysterious moon Titan , where it will plunge into the hazy atmosphere and descend by parachute while its science instruments and cameras make observations .", 'The Cassini mission is a joint project of NASA , ESA and the Italian space agency .', 'http : //www.nasa.gov/cassini', "Titan is a key target of Cassini 's $ 3.3 billion ( euro2.4 billion ) mission to study the Saturn system , which includes its spectacular rings and numerous moons ."]}, {'file_name': 'LTW_ENG_20041225.0002', 'file_top_sent': ["The Frisbee-shaped Huygens probe successfully separated from the Cassini spacecraft Friday and began a risky 2.5-million-mile journey to the surface of Saturn 's bizarre , smog-choked moon Titan .", "`` Today 's release was another successful milestone in the Cassini-Huygens odyssey , '' said David Southwood of the European Space Agency , which built the Huygens probe .", 'In late October , Cassini passed within 745 miles of the surface of Titan .', "That data wo n't come for another three weeks , during which time the 9-foot-diameter Huygens probe will chase down Titan and then , if everything goes as planned , hurl itself through the thick , nitrogen-methane atmosphere before crashing into a surface that could consist of anything from a sticky chemical sludge to poison oceans .", 'Answering those questions is the job of Huygens , a 700-pound collection of scientific instruments designed to sniff and measure the atmosphere of Titan as it streaks to the surface .']}, {'file_name': 'NYT_ENG_20041222.0130', 'file_top_sent': ["Fr